<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--LovelornBusinessman     04-27 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Lovelorn Businessman,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Businessman Shells Out $3,744 For Full-Page Personal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small slot in the personals section was not
enough for Jean-Claude, a lovelorn businessman who took a full page
in a Geneva newspaper to seek out his dream woman _ to the tune of
$3,744.
   ``I am looking for a very special woman who would like to share
adventures and a taste of the high life with me on an occasional
basis,'' said the advertisement placed Wednesday in the La Suisse
daily by Jean-Claude, who identified himself only by his first name.
   A spokesman for the newspaper said it was the most expensive
personal it had ever printed.
   The 39-year-old Geneva businessman, who said he was recovering
from a broken relationship, told The Associated Press the
advertisement was no joke.
   Jean-Claude said the successful applicant would find him a
``generous and creative'' person offering presents of jewels,
flowers, clothes and exotic holidays.
