<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--GroomSentenced     04-27 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Groom Sentenced,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Groom Gets Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The groom left in handcuffs and the bride
left in tears after a judge presided over their wedding and then
sentenced the man to 13 years in prison on a cocaine conviction.
   Alex J. Pedrin's 8-year-old daughter and 4-year-old son by a
previous marriage sat impassively next to their grandmother as
their handcuffed father was led away after being sentenced
Wednesday by Judge Nanette Warner of Pima County Superior Court.
   However, Pedrin's new wife, 28-year-old Belinda Hoefert, who is
expecting his child in September, began crying softly when the
sentence was announced and left the courtroom in tears.
   Under state law, the 31-year-old Pedrin must serve the full team
because a plea bargain with prosecutors required him to admit to a
previous conviction for burglary.
   Pedrin's first wife was stabbed to death in February 1987. A
friend of the couple was convicted of murder and sentenced to death
for the killing.
</TEXT>
