<FIRST>r i PM-Colgate-Robbery     04-27 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Colgate-Robbery,0216</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gang Steals Toiletries From Colgate Palmolive Factory In Italy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANZIO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twenty bandits armed with pistols and
machine guns raided a Colgate Palmolive factory today and escaped
with $740,000 worth of soap, toothpaste, bubble bath and shampoo,
police and company officials said.
   The bandits, who arrived with a dozen trucks to transport their
loot, burst into the factory in this seaside city 35 miles south of
Rome shortly after midnight, police said.
   The bandits locked about 80 workers in a company truck and at
gunpoint forced another 20 workers to load up the gang's trucks
with the toilet articles. The gang then forced the rest of the
workers into the company truck and drove off, according to the
police account.
   ``The bandits were calm and very professional. They looked
through the lists of merchandise to decide what they wanted to
steal,'' the Italian news agency ANSA quoted an unidentified
company employee as saying.
   Police said the gang remained in the plant for about four hours.
The workers freed themselves about a half hour later and called
police.
   A spokesman for the U.S.-owned company confirmed the police
report.
   Police speculated that the robbers may have been members of the
Camorra, an organized crime syndicate based in Naples.
</TEXT>
