<DATELINE>MILL VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British rockers Nick Lowe and Elvis
Costello lead the chorus at a 21st anniversary gathering for
Village Music, a tiny second-hand record shop frequented by music
stars.
   The store, 10 miles from San Francisco, is jammed with owner
John Goddard's collection of vintage rock and soul posters.
   The parade of music legends that performed Monday included Jerry
Garcia and Bob Weir of the Grateful Dead, Sammy Hagar of Van Halen,
Kim Wilson of the Fabulous Thunderbirds, Pete Sears of the Starship
