<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--US-Climbers     04-27 0108</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--US-Climbers,0111</SECOND>
<HEAD>American Women Climb Mount Pumori</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three women from the United States have
climbed Nepal's 23,488-foot Mount Pumori, the Tourism Ministry said
Thursday.
   Carol Snetsinger, 27, and Lucylle Smith, 37, both of Lander,
Wyo., and Kathleen Phibbs, 31, of Seattle, reached the summit
Tuesday, the ministry said. They returned safely to a camp at
21,156 feet later the same day, the ministry said.
   The three were among eight climbers _ seven of them women _ in a
team led by Sharon Kearney, 37, also a teacher from Lander. The
remaining team members were still trying to reach the summit, the
ministry said.
</TEXT>
