<HEAD>Police Seize 10 Tons of Hashish</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VENICE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police seized 10 tons of pure hashish in
two containers that were shipped to this Italian port city from
Pakistan, officials said Thursday.
   Police discovered the drugs after plant fibers were found
sticking from a false bottom in one of the containers, stored in a
port warehouse.
   The wholesale value of the drugs was estimated at $7.7 million.
   The containers had been sent to Venice from Karachi, in
Pakistan, aboard the Yugoslav freighter Buzet, police said. No
arrests were reported.
