<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--AbortionProtest     04-27 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Abortion Protest,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Linked-Arm Barricade Results In More Than 100 Arrests</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKELAND, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 100 anti-abortion demonstrators
were arrested Thursday after linking arms to block the doors at the
Women's Health Center, police said.
   ``They had a crowd of 250 to 350 people, and they effectively
barricaded the entrance to the women's clinic,'' police Sgt. Chuck
Smith said. The demonstration came a day after the U.S. Supreme
Court heard arguments in a case that could limit abortions.
   One man suffered arm and facial abrasions when he slipped from
the grasp of police officers who picked him up to remove him. Most
of those arrested were released soon afterward, but some refused to
identify themselves and were kept in custody.
   The clinic reopened by noon.
   ``Some of our patients were delayed in getting inside the
clinic, but they've all be taken care of now,'' clinic
administrator Carolyn Maxwell said.
   The protest was organized by a local group called Christians
Against Abortion. It is affiliated with Operation Rescue, a group
that has staged similar demonstrations across the nation.
</TEXT>
