<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavyweight boxing champion Mike Tyson
received a speeding ticket accusing him of driving 71 mph in a 30
mph zone, police said.
   Officers pursued Tyson late Wednesday night as the boxer, in his
1989 Lamborghini, raced against a friend on a four-lane avenue.
After a brief chase, police caught up with Tyson and the other
driver, 22-year-old Mark Johnson of Albany, when they pulled into a
parking lot.
   ``We asked them for their license and registration,'' said
arresting Officer George Maloney. ``They didn't have much to say.
He (Tyson) said he just arrived in town.''
   Tyson, 22, and Maloney were both charged with speeding and were
scheduled to appear in Albany City Court on May 9.
