<FIRST>r f PM-Tandy-Panasonic     04-27 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Tandy-Panasonic,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tandy Says Will Produce Laptops With Panasonic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tandy Corp. says it will make a laptop
computer that will be sold worldwide under the Radio Shack and
Panasonic brand names under a deal with Matsushita Electric
Industrial Co. Ltd.
   The laptop deal was announced Wednesday as Tandy dedicated a
factory in Fort Worth where the company will produce full-size
personal computers under a deal with Japan's Matsushita, which uses
the Panasonic brand name.
   Tandy Chairman John V. Roach did not reveal the projected price,
size or design of the new laptop.
   Roach also said the company is negotiating with other laptop
vendors over patents held by Tandy subsidiary Grid.
   Grid ``believes it has fundamental patents for portable
computers that will potentially need to be licensed by other
portable manufacturers,'' according to a statement from the company.
   Roach gave few details, except to say that the patents involved
machines where screens folded down.
</TEXT>
