<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sara Lee,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Food Giant Reports Record Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sara Lee Corp. on Thursday announced record
third-quarter earnings of $95 million, up 23.4 percent from the
same period last year, on record sales of $2.84 billion.
   ``Our third-quarter sales and earning gains reflect the strong
operational trends that Sara Lee enjoyed throughout the first half
of fiscal 1989,'' said John H. Bryan Jr., chairman and chief
executive, in a statement.
   The earnings for the period ended April 1 amounted to 80 cents
per share compared with 66 cents per share on $77 million in
earnings last year.
   The sales figure was an increase of 14.2 percent from last
year's $2.48 billion.
   For the first nine months of fiscal 1989, Sara Lee officials
said, net sales increased 15.1 percent _ to $8.66 billion from last
year's $7.53 billion. Net income climbed to $307.8 million, a 29.3
percent increase over the $238 million reported last year.
   Earnings per share for the nine-month period increased 26.9
percent _ to $2.64 from the $2.08 per share a year earlier.
   Sara Lee is an international food and comsumer packaged good
company with annual sales exceeding $10 billion.
