<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose sharply again Thursday on
continued optimism that British interest rates will not go higher
for the time being.
   Sparking the market's latest bout of enthusiasm was Wednesday's
news of a sharp narrowing of the British trade deficit in March,
bettering most market expectations.
   Also giving the overall market a boost were better-than-expected
first-quarter earnings results from Imperial Chemical Industries
PLC, generally considered a bellwether of British industrial
performance.
