<FIRST>r f BC-PlasticBags     04-27 0230</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Plastic Bags,0240</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reynolds' New Bags Latest Effort To Insulate Firm From Cyclical Declines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reynolds Metals Co. Thursday introduced a line
of plastic storage bags, continuing its strategy of focusing on
consumer products to help insulate the big aluminum maker from
cyclical declines in aluminum markets.
   The Richmond, Va.-based company unveiled a 10-item line of
Reynolds Sure-Seal reclosable plastic bags at a New York news
conference.
   The sandwich, food storage and freezer bags were described as
the most durable ones that will be available in the $500 million
market and they have a ``triple track'' closure designed to provide
a tight seal for freshness, leak resistance and ease of opening and
closing.
   Earlier this year, Reynolds expanded its plastic wrap line by
introducing colored versions.
   Reynolds has been expanding its consumer products business for
several years, acquiring in the process Cut-Rite wax paper, Baker's
Choice paper products and Presto products.
   ``We have followed that strategy with great care and
attention,'' said William O. Bourke, Reynolds chairman and chief
executive.
   ``These are high-added value, recession-resistant products,'' he
said in a prepared statement. ``They help insulate our company from
the ups and downs of a cyclical world aluminum market.''
   Reynolds is one of the nation's largest aluminum manufacturers,
a precious metals producer and consumer products company. Its most
widely known consumer product is Reynolds Wrap aluminum foil.
</TEXT>
